text: @FedEx help me understand why my delivery from Utah has to travel to TN to get WA? Don't you have resources on the West  Coast?
@ManzTony Hi, this is Robin. Iâ€™d be happy to look into your concerns.  Please DM your name, address, city, state, zip code, tracking number, phone number, and email address. https://t.co/7vnSkvqx3r
@FedExHelp I saw the tracking. I'm curious to know why would you east when the package is only one time zone away, rather travel two more?

@ManzTony For packages shipped via our Express service. To move packages as efficiently as possibly, FedEx operates a hub-and-spoke system of transportation with Memphis as one of our central sorting facilities. ~Robin
@FedExHelp So you're telling me a big company like yours, has one sorting facility? https://t.co/nAEPp8d58m
@ManzTony Memphis is one of our major sorting hubs. Our other hubs are located in Oakland, Newark, Fort Worth, Indianapolis and Anchorage. ~ Robin
@FedExHelp So why didn't they just use Oakland coming from Utah?
@ManzTony We have no way to know which hub shipments will be routed to or the logistics involved. ~ Robin
@ManzTony Is there a delay on your shipment?  ~ Robin
@FedExHelp No, just curious why it was processed this way. Thank you.
@FedExHelp You'd think someone would come up w a better sorting system,  or did I just did for you!
